Key Match Events: Turkey's Merih Demiral scored two goals, one from a deflected corner and another from a direct header.
Austria's Michael Gregoritsch scored a goal from a corner flicked on by Stefan Posch.
Mert Gunok made a stunning save in the 94th minute to prevent the match from going to extra time.
Post-Match Reflections: Austria exits the Euros at the same stage as in the previous tournament.
Turkey's lack of tactical intelligence was highlighted despite their entertaining play.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Heavy rain in Leipzig affected the match, exaggerating slide tackles and adding to the chaos.
Both sets of supporters threw objects onto the pitch, with a coin from the Turkish end striking Austria’s Marcel Sabitzer on the head.
Turkey's Arda Guler was pelted with cups thrown from the stands.
